#Face #BQFace #Icon #blackAngel #Carta #MiyakeMugler #Porcelain #WorldAidsBallCanada #Ballroom #Legendary
Merry Christmas to All! 🎅🏾

In an instant, my heart is shattered into a million pieces.  Daddy, the pain I’m feeling is like no other.  You were something so special, not just to me, but the world and community got to experience the joy and sunshine of who I called my father.  I can’t put into words how great of a father and a person you were.  Let’s just say, I got lucky.  Although you left so suddenly, our last conversation, our laughs, your smile, making you drink your water, on yesterday will be forever etched in my brain.  There’s so much to process, but I promise to be as strong as I can to understand.  Fact is I’m lost, but I’ll find my way soon.  I love you beyond life itself and will miss you and everything about you.  I wish i had a sign so I could’ve had time to tell you goodbye.  Some how God saw it fit to happen differently and I’ll try not to question that.  You are my everything and I just thank God for giving me you as a father and all of the beautiful years we had together will live with me forever.  Until we meet again…

Rest in Heaven,
Love Lil Hook 💔😭🕊️

What a time it will be.  Daddy we are going to do it big in the name of your legacy! 💜💛🕊️
#Hook

THE CAT IS OUT! 
Category Is : Drama! I’m very excited to announce that I am a part of this ground breaking new series…

From @variety : ITV America (“Queer Eye”) and Good Company (https://variety.com/t/good-company/) (Beyonce’s “Lemonade”) have announced new unscripted series “Category Is (https://variety.com/t/category-is/)” (working title), an eight-episode documentary series focusing on New York City’s Ballroom scene through the lens of one of its most prominent houses: The House of Miyake-Mugler.
Executive produced by Yusef Williams (“Overall Father” of the House of Miyake-Mugler), the series chronicles the personal and professional lives of nine members of this all-Black and queer “chosen family.” Power struggles, romance and interpersonal rivalries abound as they battle to make names for themselves in the House, the Ballroom scene and around the world, smashing
 stereotypes and overcoming tremendous adversity.
Full story on Variety.com
